docs.abstract: Applying behavioral economics, John Hancock is offering a discount on life insurance and other incentives to customers with healthy lifestyles.
docs.snippet: Applying behavioral economics, John Hancock is offering a discount on life insurance and other incentives to customers with healthy lifestyles.
docs.lead_paragraph: Brian and Carla Restid, a couple in their mid-60s, bought life insurance four years ago to protect their lifestyle in retirement. A year later, they upgraded to a pilot program offered by the insurer to get fitter, healthier and more energized.

headline.main: Life Insurance Offering More Incentive to Live Longer
headline.print_headline: Life Insurance Offering More Incentive to Live Longer

docs.abstract: Diane Greene, the head of Google’s Cloud business, is said to have told employees that it was backing away from the A.I. work with the military.
docs.snippet: Diane Greene, the head of Google’s Cloud business, is said to have told employees that it was backing away from the A.I. work with the military.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Google, hoping to head off a rebellion by employees upset that the technology they were working on could be used for lethal purposes, will not renew a contract with the Pentagon for artificial intelligence work when a current deal expires next year.

headline.main: Google Will Not Renew Pentagon Contract That Upset Employees

docs.abstract: The Danish toymaker has relied on oil-based plastics for over 50 years. It wants to give them up by 2030. Finding alternatives is a vast project.
docs.snippet: The Danish toymaker has relied on oil-based plastics for over 50 years. It wants to give them up by 2030. Finding alternatives is a vast project.
docs.lead_paragraph: BILLUND, Denmark — At the heart of this town lies a building that is a veritable temple to the area’s most famous creation, the humble Lego brick. It is filled with complex creations, from a 50-foot tree to a collection of multicolored dinosaurs, all of them built with a product that has barely changed in more than 50 years.

headline.main: Lego Wants to Completely Remake Its Toy Bricks (Without Anyone Noticing)
headline.print_headline: Lego Hunts New Bricks  For a Sustainable Future

docs.abstract: The Danish company’s acquisition of the Rhode Island-based Deepwater Wind is a sign that the United States is growing in appeal to clean energy developers.
docs.snippet: The Danish company’s acquisition of the Rhode Island-based Deepwater Wind is a sign that the United States is growing in appeal to clean energy developers.
docs.lead_paragraph: Orsted, a Danish company that is one of the world’s largest offshore wind energy developers, said on Monday that it would acquire a Rhode Island rival, Deepwater Wind, for $510 million, a sign that the United States is becoming an attractive market for offshore energy generators.

headline.main: Orsted, a Giant in Offshore Wind Farms, Makes a Move in the U.S.
headline.print_headline: Danish Wind Giant Pays $510 Million for Rival, Signaling Appeal of U.S. Market

docs.abstract: Tying recent growth to his policy moves, the president offered broad pronouncements and a litany of statistics. Some were well founded, others less so.
docs.snippet: Tying recent growth to his policy moves, the president offered broad pronouncements and a litany of statistics. Some were well founded, others less so.
docs.lead_paragraph: When President Trump announced Friday that the American economy had grown at an annual rate of 4.1 percent in the second quarter — an achievement he called “amazing” —  he included a long list of statements about how well the economy has performed on his watch.

headline.main: Trump’s Numbers on ‘Amazing’ Economy Sometimes Don’t Add Up
headline.print_headline: The Data Was Good, But Not ‘Historic’

docs.abstract: Kevin Systrom and Mike Krieger, Instagram’s co-founders, resigned from the photo app on Monday. Their exits add to the challenges facing Facebook, which owns the app.
docs.snippet: Kevin Systrom and Mike Krieger, Instagram’s co-founders, resigned from the photo app on Monday. Their exits add to the challenges facing Facebook, which owns the app.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Kevin Systrom and Mike Krieger, the co-founders of the photo-sharing app Instagram, have resigned and plan to leave the company in the coming weeks, adding to the challenges facing Instagram’s parent company, Facebook.

headline.main: Instagram’s Co-Founders to Step Down From Company
headline.print_headline: Co-Founders Of Instagram Are Departing The Company
